        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Step 1: Getting Started with CapCut",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l1",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://capcut.com"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "To begin, head to ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "capcut.com",
            "marks": [
              "l1"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " and grab the app for your device—iOS, Android, Windows, or Mac. The interface is super intuitive; you'll feel right at home even if you're new to editing. Start a new project by tapping the \"+\" button and importing your clips from your gallery or cloud storage. CapCut supports a ton of formats, so no compatibility headaches here.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l2",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/what-is-capcut"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you're curious about its origins, check out ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
