            "text": "what CapCut is",
            "marks": [
              "l2"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " on our site for more details.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Step 2: Using Auto Captions and AI Tools",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "This is where CapCut shines. Go to the \"Text\" menu and select \"Auto Captions\"—it analyzes your audio and generates accurate subtitles in seconds. No more manual typing! The AI also offers features like background removal and scene detection, which I use to streamline my workflow. For instance, I recently edited a vlog where auto captions saved me over an hour.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Pro tip: Experiment with the AI-powered effects for dynamic transitions. It's like having a virtual editor assistant.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Step 3: Applying Effects and Templates",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "CapCut's library is packed with trendy templates and effects perfect for social media. Browse the \"Templates\" tab to find viral-style edits for TikTok or Instagram. Simply drag and drop your clips into a template, and it auto-adjusts timing and effects. I love how this helps me create polished content in minutes—no design skills needed.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l3",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/capcut-use-cases"
          }
        ],
